---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SchemaMarkup from '../components/SchemaMarkup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Northsake — Our Story and Approach"
  description="Northsake builds AI visibility infrastructure for consulting firms. Learn about our approach to SEO, GEO, and why we focus exclusively on firms that sell expertise."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'About', url: '/about' },
  ]}
>
  <SchemaMarkup
    type="person"
    data={{
      name: 'Agrim Goyal',
      jobTitle: 'Founder',
      description: 'Founder of Northsake, building AI visibility infrastructure for consulting firms.',
      url: 'https://northsake.com/about',
    }}
  />

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="content-container pt-16 md:pt-28 pb-24 md:pb-36">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
      <p class="section-number mb-8">About Northsake</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl text-ns-text leading-tight mb-8">
        Visibility should be<br />
        <span class="italic text-ns-accent">built, not bought.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="prose-ns max-w-2xl">
        We started Northsake with a simple observation: the consulting firms with the deepest
        expertise weren't the ones getting found. The firms winning on visibility were the ones
        who treated it as infrastructure, not an afterthought.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ===== THE STORY ===== -->
  <section class="content-container py-24 md:py-36" aria-labelledby="story-heading">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-6xl md:text-8xl font-bold text-ns-border select-none" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
        <h2 id="story-heading" class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-ns-text mt-4">
          How we got here.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 lg:col-start-6 pt-4 space-y-6">
        <p class="prose-ns">
          I watched a consulting firm with exceptional talent lose a major engagement to a competitor
          whose primary advantage was showing up first — in Google results, in AI-generated recommendations,
          in every channel where the client was doing their research.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-ns">
          The better firm had better people, better methodology, better track record. But none of
          that mattered because the client never found them. By the time they entered the conversation,
          the decision was already shaped by whoever the algorithms surfaced first.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-ns">
          That's the problem Northsake exists to solve. Not with quick fixes or keyword tricks,
          but by building the kind of visibility infrastructure that compounds — that makes your
          expertise findable, citable, and authoritative across every channel where your future
          clients are looking.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ===== OUR APPROACH ===== -->
  <section class="content-container py-24 md:py-36" aria-labelledby="approach-heading">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-6xl md:text-8xl font-bold text-ns-border select-none" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
        <h2 id="approach-heading" class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-ns-text mt-4">
          How we think about visibility.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 lg:col-start-6 pt-4">
        <div class="space-y-12">
          {[
            {
              title: 'Infrastructure over campaigns',
              body: 'Campaigns end. Infrastructure compounds. Every piece of work we do is designed to build on itself — creating durable visibility that grows stronger with time, not a temporary spike that fades.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Dual-channel visibility',
              body: 'Google and AI engines evaluate content differently. We optimize for both simultaneously — structured for search, authored for citation. Your firm shouldn\'t have to choose between being ranked and being cited.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Expertise-first content',
              body: 'We don\'t write thin content to hit keyword targets. We work with firms to surface and structure the expertise they already have — the insights, frameworks, and perspectives that demonstrate real authority.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Measurement over promises',
              body: 'We track what matters: search positions, AI citation frequency, referral quality, and pipeline influence. Every engagement starts with a NorthScore and every month shows measurable progress against it.',
            },
          ].map((principle) => (
            <div class="border-l-2 border-ns-border pl-8 hover:border-ns-accent transition-colors duration-300">
              <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-ns-text text-lg mb-3">{principle.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-ns-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{principle.body}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ===== FOUNDER ===== -->
  <section class="content-container py-24 md:py-36" aria-labelledby="founder-heading">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <span class="font-mono text-6xl md:text-8xl font-bold text-ns-border select-none" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
      <h2 id="founder-heading" class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-ns-text mt-4 mb-12">
        Who's behind this.
      </h2>
      <div class="border border-ns-border p-8 md:p-12">
        <p class="font-sans font-semibold text-ns-text text-xl mb-2">Agrim Goyal</p>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ns-accent mb-6">Founder, Northsake</p>
        <p class="text-ns-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          I build at the intersection of AI, search, and content strategy. Northsake is where
          I channel that into something specific: making consulting firms visible in a world
          where both humans and machines decide who gets found.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
  <section class="content-container py-32 md:py-44 text-center">
    <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl text-ns-text mb-8 italic">
      Interested in working together?
    </h2>
    <p class="prose-ns max-w-xl mx-auto mb-12">
      Every engagement starts with a conversation. Tell us about your firm and where you want your visibility to go.
    </p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
      Start a Conversation
      <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
